roblem of Presence makes important contributions to the anthropology of Christianity, the history of religions in Africa, semiotics, and material culture studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aafrica.  aanthropologists.  aapostolics.  abible.  achristianity.  achurch history.  acomparative religion.  ademographic studies.  adivine union.  aethnographers.  afaith and spirituality.  afriday masowe.  aglobal christians.  agods presence.  ahistorical ethnography.  aholy spirit.  amediation.  anonfiction.  apersonal authority.  areligious anthropology.  areligious authority.  areligious faith.  areligious practices.  areligious scholars.  areligious studies.  ascriptures.  asemiotics.  aspiritual world.  aworld religions.  azimbabwe.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094004840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940048423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520940048/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles